 of Beattie=E2=80=99s appointment.) Some senators are perturbed that Beatti=
e, at least for the time being, will be serving in a critical, public-facin=
g job at State=E2=80=94a job once held by the legendary, longtime, trusted
George W. Bush adviser Karen Hughes. If he were officially nominated, Beatt=
ie might be difficult to confirm=E2=80=94even in a Senate that seems to be =
waving through Trump=E2=80=99s most controversial nominees.

